{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efd7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3056c"},"text":"§ 3056c.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Interagency cooperation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efd8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Consultation with the Assistant Secretary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall consult with and obtain the written views of the Assistant Secretary before issuing rules and before establishing general policy in the administration of this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efd9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Consultation with heads of other agencies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall consult and cooperate with the Secretary of Health and Human Services (acting through officers including the Director of the Office of Community Services), and the heads of other Federal agencies that carry out programs related to the program carried out under this subchapter, in order to achieve optimal coordination of the program carried out under this subchapter with such related programs. Each head of a Federal agency shall cooperate with the Secretary in disseminating information relating to the availability of assistance under this subchapter and in promoting the identification and interests of individuals eligible for employment in projects assisted under this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efda-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Coordination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efdb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall promote and coordinate efforts to carry out projects under this subchapter jointly with programs, projects, or activities carried out under other Acts, especially activities provided under the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act, including activities provided through one-stop delivery systems established under section 121(e) of such Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3151/e"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 3151(e)","children":[],"tail":"], that provide training and employment opportunities to eligible individuals."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efdc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056c/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Coordination with certain activities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall consult with the Secretary of Education to promote and coordinate efforts to carry out projects under this subchapter jointly with activities in which eligible individuals may participate that are carried out under the Carl D. Perkins Career and Technical Education Act of 2006 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s2301"},"text":"20 U.S.C. 2301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc63efdd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/73/tV/s505"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–73, title V, § 505","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/365/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–365, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2575"},"text":"120 Stat. 2575","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/tV/s512/w/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128, title V, § 512(w)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1715"},"text":"128 Stat. 1715","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc63efde-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc63efdf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc63efe0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(1), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1425"},"text":"128 Stat. 1425","children":[],"tail":", which enacted chapter 32 (§ 3101 et seq.) of Title 29, Labor, repealed chapter 30 (§ 2801 et seq.) of Title 29 and chapter 73 (§ 9201 et seq.) of Title 20, Education, and made amendments to numerous other sections and notes in the Code. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3101"},"text":"section 3101 of Title 29","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Carl D. Perkins Career and Technical Education Act of 2006, referred to in subsec. (c)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/210"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–210","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/403"},"text":"77 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":", as amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/270/s1/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–270, § 1(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-08-12"},"text":"Aug. 12, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/683"},"text":"120 Stat. 683","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 44 (§ 2301 et seq.) of Title 20, Education. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s2301"},"text":"section 2301 of Title 20","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idbc63efe1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"